value.0:
The sureforged Kukri Dicey wielded upon the day of his death, recovered from the scene just days after the incident. It appeared before the gates of the town one early morning; inscribed with dark initials along the pommel. 

"D.Q"

An elusive figure of feminine dimensions, she stands at the approximate height of Halfling kin. Her frame is hugged by a wreath of swarthy shadow which extends along her back to form graceful wings. She appears to be surrounded by a number of eclecticly placed items, perched upon shining stacks of gold coin - not a single one sullied or touched, and not a single coin less than it was the last you may have seen it. 

As you approach and reach out with your hand, inky tendrils of umbral energy swirl through the thick cavern air and stick to your flesh. It begins to swallow your body in shadow, until you step out of the idol's vicinity.
A round, shimmering rogue stone said to have once belonged to the elusive 'Tiger' Lilly, Child Prodigy of Bendir Dale. Upon Dicey's death, she gave the stone unto the shrine in Dicey's honor.

A crude depiction, perhaps done by the hand of a child, of a haunting image; the sight of a burial, a freshly interred grave. The tombstone that stands before it bears no name or indication of who is to be layed "six underground".
A crude picture of a Hin wearing black and grey laying in a grassy field with a Kukri lodged in their chest. Red paint smothered all over them... you can only assume it's blood.
A drawing of a Hin wearing pink and white, stood before a house with crudely drawn fire erupting from it.
"The time is soon coming..." A voice faintly whispers as you enter.
